      "text": "Building a startup is hard. You need to find product-market fit, build a team, \nand iterate quickly. The key is to talk to customers constantly and ship fast. Don't overthink it - just build something people want. As a founder, your job is to make sure the company survives. That means being \nruthless about priorities. Focus on the one metric that matters most. Everything \nelse is a distraction. Move fast and break things, but talk to users first. The best founders are problem solvers.",
